original: Johansson, Per John Rohert, kyrkoherde, Veddige, f. 27/8/97 i Staf-singe. Hall. 1. G. 27 m. Ellen Lindeberg. Barn: Per Daniel f. 28, Ruth 30, Gunnel 31, Ingegerd 33. — Stud:ex. i Gbg 18, teol. kand. 22, prakt. teol. ex. 23, prästv. s. å. V. kommin. o. pastoTsadj. i Torup 23-27,, kommin. i Veddige 27-33, kyrkoh. där. fr. 32. Ordf. i Veddige kyrkostämma o. past:-kyrkost., i Sällstorps kyrkost., i skolråd, i RK-krets.
translated: Johansson, Per John Rohert, clergyman, Veddige, born on August 27, 1897 in Stafsinge, Halland. Married on August 27, 19XX to Ellen Lindeberg. Children: Per Daniel born in 1928, Ruth born in 1930, Gunnel born in 1931, Ingegerd born in 1933. Completed studies: high school in Gothenburg in 1918, theology degree in 1922, practical theology degree in 1923, ordained as a priest the same year. Served as assistant pastor and pastor in Torup from 1923 to 1927, then as a pastor in Veddige from 1927 to 1933, becoming the parish vicar in 1932. Served as chairman of the Veddige parish council, pastor parish council, Sällstorp parish council and school board, as well as in the RK district.
